parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering damper can cause the vehicle to wobble or shake uncontrollably, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or wobbles
the vehicle vibrates
and the front end feels unstable
especially when driving at high speeds or over bumps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The power steering fails or becomes difficult to use
the steering wheel feels heavy or hard to turn
and warning lights may appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of steering components, such as the track bar bracket, can cause the vehicle to lose control and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's steering feels unstable or loose
and there may be unusual noises or vibrations coming from the front end.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of electrical systems or components can cause a range of problems, including loss of power steering, warning lights, and other issues that can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Warning lights appear on the dashboard
the vehicle's systems malfunction
and there may be unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or even catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
burning odor
smoke
or fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or even catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission slips out of gear
grinding sound
abnormal noise
loss of power
vehicle fails to properly accelerate
transmission warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Train Failure and Recall Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power train can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or even catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries. The recall issues can lead to a delay in the repair, causing further safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle is unable to shift into gear
transmission warning light is illuminated
service transmission warning light is illuminated
auto start warning light is illuminated
burning odor
smoke
or fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the loss of power steering, brakes, and other critical systems, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Multiple warning lights on the dashboard
loss of power steering
loss of brakes
inability to shift gears
and unexpected changes in vehicle behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Uconnect system can cause distractions, loss of critical systems, and unexpected changes in vehicle behavior, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Unwanted changes in radio stations
navigation
and climate control
as well as the delamination of the touchscreen display.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear defroster can cause the rear window to shatter, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Burn marks on the rear window
shattered rear window
and failure of the rear defroster.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and inability to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auto start/stop system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
and failure of the auto start/stop system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera can cause accidents or injuries, especially when reversing.
symptoms: Intermittent or complete failure of the backup camera.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter system can cause the vehicle to lose power or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Inability to shift gears
service shifter warning message
and loss of power steering.
